  "text": "Example 6.1. Let S = CP n with the standard Kähler structure. As discussed in [CITATION_1] , by taking L trivial (which means that L 1,0 = O(1))by qFK we obtain Z = CP 2n+1 which is the twistor space of the quaternionic projective space. In this case we consider affine sections of O(1, −1) along the leaves of the (1, 0)-foliation, hence by Remark 5.1 it should mean that in the construction we obtain Z by gluing two copies of the bundle O(1) ⊗ C 2n+1 over CP n using the blow down from P(O(−1, 0)⊕O(0, −1)). Indeed, fixing a projective n-space S in CP 2n+1 there is a natural embedding of the bundle O(1) ⊗ C 2n+1 into CP 2n+1 such that S is the zero section: denoting points in CP ",
